<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<!--
Gate 2 — admin-level failure at ca:country outside civic coverage → <redirect>.

Country code CA (Canada) has no provisioned boundary and no civic coverage
region entry in this LVF deployment. The progressive filter fails at ca:country.
The civic coverage lookup for the submitted admin tuple also yields no match —
CA is entirely outside this LVF's coverage region.

Because LVF_PARENT_URI is configured and the failure is at an admin element
outside coverage, the response is <redirect> pointing to the parent LVF rather
than <locationValidation> with <invalid> at ca:country.

Companion to G2-SSAP-INVALID-COUNTRY-001 and RESP-MAPPING-DEFAULT-001, which
documented the same GIS-level failure before the redirect rule was added. Those
tests now also return <redirect> since the behavior of an out-of-coverage admin
failure changed globally.
-->
<findService xmlns="urn:ietf:params:xml:ns:lost1" validateLocation="true">
  <location id="L1" profile="civic">
    <civicAddress xmlns="urn:ietf:params:xml:ns:pidf:geopriv10:civicAddr">
      <country>CA</country>
      <A1>BC</A1>
      <A2>Metro Vancouver</A2>
      <A3>Vancouver</A3>
      <RD>Main</RD>
      <STS>Street</STS>
      <HNO>100</HNO>
    </civicAddress>
  </location>
  <service>urn:service:sos</service>
</findService>
